59,"reg":460},"ἔτια","ἔτη",[462,465],{"_":463,"ref":464},"·","#interpunct",{"_":463,"ref":464},{"orig":467,"reg":472},{"_":468,"lb":469},"ἄμεμτος",{"n":470,"break":471},"4","no","ἄμεμπτος",{"_":474,"value":475},"εἴκοσι","20",{"type":477,"resp":416,"listApp":478},"apparatus",{"app":479},[480,482,485],{"note":481},"Text based on photographs",{"loc":483,"note":484},"line 4","Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz, Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel: αἴζως (i.e. ἔζης); Korhonen: αἴζωσ(εν)",{"loc":486,"note":487},"line 5","Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz ἔτι α εἴκοσι; Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel, Korhonen: ἔτια",{"type":489,"xml:lang":192,"resp":416,"p":490},"translation","Markia Loukilia, honest and blameless, lived for 20 years.",{"type":489,"xml:lang":353,"resp":416,"p":492},"Markia Loukilia, onesta e irreprensibile, visse 20 anni.",{"type":494,"p":495},"commentary",{"_":496,"foreign":497},"The epitaph has the traditional structure with the name of the deceased, the epithets  (for which, see Korhonen 2004: 84) and the indication of the age, with the verb  in the aorist form. Following Korhonen, the phonetic reading  for  seems to be less probable than  or  (from ): for a similar form, see Libertini NSA 1931: 391-392 (). Also the reading  seems to be less probable (despite  of the Christian epitaph Libertini 1931: 45 nr. 10) than the phonetic reading  (i.g. ): see IC IV 168*. The Doricism at l. 3 and the hypercorrection at l. 4 denote the stonecutter’s quest for refinement or poor knowledge of Greek (as also revealed by  of l. 5).",[498,500,502,504,506,508,510,512,514,516,518,519,521],{"_":499,"xml:lang":106},"χρηστὰ καὶ ἄμεμπτος",{"_":501,"xml:lang":106},"ζάω",{"_":503,"xml:lang":106},"αἴζως",{"_":505,"xml:lang":106},"ἔζης",{"_":507,"xml:lang":106},"αἴζωσ’",{"_":509,"xml:lang":106},"αἴζωσ(εν)",{"_":511,"xml:lang":106},"ζώω",{"_":513,"xml:lang":106},"ἔσζω[σ-]",{"_":515,"xml:lang":106},"ἔτι α εἴκοσι",{"_":517,"xml:lang":106},"ἔτι",{"_":459,"xml:lang":106},{"_":520,"xml:lang":106},"ἔτεα",{"_":459,"xml:lang":106},{"type":523,"listBibl":524},"bibliography",[525,553],{"type":108,"bibl":526},[527,530,533,536,539,544,547,550],{"author":111,"date":112,"citedRange":113,"ptr":528,"ref":529},{"target":115},{"_":117,"target":117},{"author":111,"date":119,"citedRange":120,"ptr":531,"ref":532},{"target":122},{"_":124,"target":124},{"author":126,"date":127,"citedRange":128,"ptr":534,"ref":535},{"target":130},{"_":132,"target":132},{"author":134,"date":135,"citedRange":136,"ptr":537,"ref":538},{"target":138},{"_":140,"target":140},{"type":142,"n":143,"citedRange":540,"ptr":542,"ref":543},{"ref":541},{"_":146,"target":147},{"target":149},{"_":151,"target":151},{"type":142,"n":153,"citedRange":154,"ptr":545,"ref":546},{"target":156},{"_":158,"target":158},{"type":142,"n":160,"citedRange":161,"ptr":548,"ref":549},{"target":163},{"_":165,"target":165},{"type":142,"n":167,"citedRange":168,"ptr":551,"ref":552},{"target":170},{"_":172,"target":172},{"type":174,"bibl":53},[555],{"n":422,"url":93,"height":423,"width":424,"desc":94,"surfaceType":419},{"title":557,"body":558,"divs":559,"images":575},"ISic001313. Epitaph for Markia Loukilia","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΜΑΡΚΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΛΟΥΚΙΛΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΧΡΗΣΤΑΚΑΙΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΕΜΤΟΣΑΙΖΩΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΤΙΑΕΙΚΟΣΙ´\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.3 reg., orig. ἄμεμτος | l.4 reg., orig. ΑΙΖΩΣαἴζωσ | l.5 reg., orig. ΕΤΙΑἔτια\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz, Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel: αἴζως (i.e. ἔζης); Korhonen: αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz ἔτι α εἴκοσι; Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel, Korhonen: ἔτια\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, honest and blameless, lived for 20 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, onesta e irreprensibile, visse 20 anni.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph has the traditional structure with the name of the deceased, the epithets \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστὰ καὶ ἄμεμπτος\u003C/span> (for which, see Korhonen 2004: 84) and the indication of the age, with the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> in the aorist form. Following Korhonen, the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζως\u003C/span> for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζης\u003C/span> seems to be less probable than \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ’\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span> (from \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζώω\u003C/span>): for a similar form, see Libertini NSA 1931: 391-392 (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔσζω[σ-]\u003C/span>). Also the reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι α εἴκοσι\u003C/span> seems to be less probable (despite \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι\u003C/span> of the Christian epitaph Libertini 1931: 45 nr. 10) than the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> (i.g. \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτεα\u003C/span>): see IC IV 168*. The Doricism at l. 3 and the hypercorrection at l. 4 denote the stonecutter’s quest for refinement or poor knowledge of Greek (as also revealed by \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> of l. 5).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1769 175 n. 69 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 186 n. 81 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 352 n. 2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Bertucci 1846 31 n. 6 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0490\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 108 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  